metadata.title: North American West Coast CTD data(supports acoustics data), 1995-present
metadata.description: Raw CTD data taken in support of acoustics sampling, various locations, usually up to 3 weeks` duration, for several years. Some continuous at one depth for duration of sampling period, other profiles to 70 or 100m at 1 h or 3 h intervals for the duration of the sampling period.
metadata.notes:
Purpose: Testing acoustical equipment; studying upper ocean processes.

Supplemental Information: Risk Justification: Data not well documented and requires knowledge to interpret.
Risk of Loss: High
Impact Justification: Data used for one time analysis.
Impact of Loss: Low
Recommended Action: Bring data to archives
Additional Info: Data from Canadian ships are on the IOS archive; data from American ships are not on the archive.

Status: In work

Maintenance frequency: None planned

Access constraints: Private

Use constraints: Data collected collaboratively. Can be made Departmentally accessible after proprietary period.
